%I A393600 #35 Mar 04 2026 19:24:52
%S A393600 23,0,41,52,70,91,126,158,216,273,386,488,675,866,1173,1526,2136,2739,
%T A393600 3755,4846
%N A393600 Maximum width of a simple imperfect squared square (SISS) of order n, or 0 if no such square exists.
%C A393600 A squared square is "simple" if it contains no smaller squared rectangle, and "imperfect" if at least two of its component squares are the same size. It is a known result that there is no Simple Imperfect Squared Square of order 14, hence a(14) = 0.
%C A393600 The nonzero terms were discovered via systematic computational evaluation of electrical network representations of planar graphs. Candidate integer square sizes are derived using Kirchhoff's Current Law. The exact (X,Y) coordinates for every square in the dissection are mapped by tracing potentials across both the primary and dual graphs. The Y-coordinates are derived from the Kirchhoff Voltage Law voltage drops across the primary graph, while the X-coordinates are explicitly calculated by tracing the potentials across the faces of the dual graph. Filtering the results to require equal total horizontal and vertical potentials (W = H) extracts the maximum bounds for perfect squares.
%D A393600 R. L. Brooks, C. A. B. Smith, A. H. Stone, and W. T. Tutte, The dissection of rectangles into squares, Duke Math. J. 7(1): 312-340 (1940).
%H A393600 Stuart E Anderson, <a href="https://www.squaring.net/sq/ss/siss/siss.html">SISS counts, bouwkampcodes, and postscript files for orders 13 to 32</a>.
%F A393600 For n >= 15, empirical logarithmic regression indicates asymptotic growth scaling at a factor of approximately 1.33 per order: W is approximately exp(0.2824*n - 0.5561).
%e A393600 For n = 13, a(13) = 23. This corresponds to the side length of the maximal 23*23 simple imperfect squared square dissected into exactly 13 squares. For n = 15, a(15) = 41, representing the maximum side length for a 15 square dissection.
%Y A393600 Cf. A002962.
%K A393600 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A393600 13,1
%A A393600 _Stuart E Anderson_, Feb 23 2026
